(27, 'Moon The Ultimate Strength Of The Horoscope', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Astrologykart.com, </strong>Our two luminaries, the Sun and the Moon, are the primary sources of nourishment on this planet. These royal planets, also known as the king and queen of our astrological system\'s planetary cabinet, are necessary for a native to live his life to the utmost. In this post, we\'ll focus on the Moon, also known as Chandrama.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Astrology and the Moon</strong></li><li>Astrologykart.com <strong>, </strong>In Vedic astrology, the planet Moon plays a crucial role in Vedic rites and beliefs. It is considered a queen and the mother\'s significator, and it is tranquil, quiet, and peaceful. The Moon is the ruler of the human mind, and persons with a powerful Moon have acute intelligence and wit.</li><li>Astrology is based on Dasa, Nakshatras, and Yogas, which are all studied in Vedic astrology from the position of a natal Moon. Yogas, on the other hand, necessitate a thorough examination of the Lagna and other planets<strong>. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with astrologer</a></strong>.</li><li>The Moon chart, also known as the Rashi chart, is an important aspect of Vedic astrology, and many experienced astrologers use it to make predictions.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Moon of Glory</strong></li><li>Until 3 degrees, the Moon is exalted in Taurus. In the birth chart, the exalted Moon has a lot of power. It imbues the individual who owns it with a very inventive and creative personality. The home, on the other hand, has its own significance. It is capable of bringing out a tremendous deal of fate, position, money, and fortune if exalted in Kendra or Trikona. </li><li><strong>The moon is sickly.</strong></li><li>The planet Moon is debilitated in Scorpio, which is exactly opposite Taurus. It is not deemed beneficial if