(35, 'Astrological benefits of reciting Gayatri Mantra regularly', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Gayatri, according to the <strong>astrologykart.com website</strong>, is the Mother of All Scriptures (Vedas). Savitri Mantra is another name for Gayatri Mantra. A devotee of Gayatri Maa has the potential to achieve significant success on the road of self-development. What counts most to this slogan is your dedication, authenticity, faith, and belief, not your colour, race, ethnicity, caste, creed, gender, or nationality.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Gayatri Mantra is a sacred mantra that is used to connect with a high level of Spiritualism. It was initially written in Vedas and is regarded the most sacred mantra. It is made up of 24 syllables that have an impact on a person\'s mental and physical health<strong>. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/astrology-advice\">Astrologer advice </a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Om, the divine energy that protects everyone, is the meaning of the Gayatri Mantra.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhoor refers to the land or the ground that sustains us.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhuvah means \"Destroyer of Sufferings,\" and he is the one who wipes away everyone\'s sorrow.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Svah is the personification of joy and satisfaction.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The highest God is referred to as Tat.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Savitur- Like the sun, bright.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Varenyam is a Sanskrit word that means \"most elevated\" or \"excellent.\"</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhargo- As pure as the Sun\'s rays.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Dev