(54, 'Lohri the Festival for Farmers', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In Northern India when the crops are harvested they celebrate the cropping and harvesting season which is also known as Lohri. The abbreviation of Lohri pronounced as (Lori) is basically said in three words like L means wood, O means dumpling and Di means dry fruits (Rewari) however the literal meaning of this abbreviation will be then L means wood, O means cow, and Di means dry fruits (Rewari). It is a way of acknowledging the change of seasons and saying thank you to God by blessing humans to see the transition in the change of the seasons and agricultural production throughout the world. Every year by the 13th of January everyone welcomes the Magh month with a great celebration across the country and different parts of the world. This festival is traditionally the biggest festival that is celebrated by our farmer families and just celebrated before Makar Sankranti. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/astrology-advice\">Astrology Advice</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Culture and its Variations in Lohri</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Every culture has different perspectives in the celebration like in Sikhism; Lohri is the festival to congratulate the newly married couples and the babies. In Sindhi culture, it is also celebrated a day before Makar Sankranti which is said as Lal Lohi.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>History about Lohri</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The Lohri was not the real name of the festival as earlier it was said as Tilodi. Lohri is formally associated with the religious faith and acknowledges the change in seasons throughout the country. On the evening of Lohri, all the people of the village or the locality gather at one place to light a bonfire and offer things like jaggery, maize, sesame, and puffed rice in the bonfire to please the fire god. The people who gathered across the bonfire also dance and sing around it in a circle. The people had an auspicious time in celebrating the festival Lohri and worship the fire god to take the blessings prosperity and happiness. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Why the festival is said Tilodi?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As in Lohri people offer sesame seeds in the fire and the Hindi translation of Sesame seeds are Til so from here it is said as Tilodi. There is also a religious point of view as sesame has a special significance as per the Garuda Purana, sesame is originated from the body of Lord Vishnu that is the reason why it is used for all the religious activities. However, as per science, it has other benefits also as per the traditional study of medicine Ayurveda putting sesame seeds in the fire eliminates many infections in the environment and circumambulates the body speeds up. This is the reason why sesame seeds (Til) are also used for religious activities like Havan and Yagya etc.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Why it is famous in Punjab?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The story of Dulla Bhatti is also associated with Lohri in Punjab as in their festival they dance in front of the bonfire and do the bhangra and during the Bhangra they sing songs and praise of Dulla Bhatti. They praise him because he used to help the needy and the poor people. Once said that Dulla Bhatti saved two orphaned girls from his uncle who sold them to the landowners. He took the charge of the two sisters and settled them down in life so on the occasion of Lohri Dulla Bhatti made them married a well-settled boy and in return bid a farewell by giving both of them two-fifty grams of sugar as a return. This is also the reason why people mostly celebrate this festival. As Lohri is marked as the New Year for the farmers of Punjab so on this day they mark the crops as their god and show their gratitude by praying and thanking the Lord Agni to bless their land with lots of abundances. By moving in the circle and doing the Parikrama they offer the dry fruit (Revadiya) with the chanting “Aadar aye diladar jaye” which means the glory of privilege comes and the poverty fades away. In this festival, the newlywed couples wear new jewelry and the newborn babies hold a comb as a part of the ritual.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>When is the right time for Lohri 2022?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>After 5 o\'clock in the evening, Rohini Nakshatra will begin so the best time for the Lohri Burning will begin at 5:43 minutes or sage 7: 25 minutes. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Lohri the Festival for Farmers', 'As per the article, the Lohri festival is in the line and the astrologers are putting the facts related to the Lohri and why it is celebrated in January, and why this festival is for farmers.', 'lohri, lohri festival, dulla bhaati, punjab, punjabi festival, punjab festival, fire, agnidev, Agni', 1, 'lohri-the-festival-for-farmers', 'festivals', 'lohri, lohri festival, dulla bhaati, punjab', '1641989979.jpg', 0, '2022-01-12 06:51:00', '2022-01-12 07:03:43'),
(55, 'Makar Sankranti the start of Fresh Beginnings', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Makar Sankranti is celebrated as the first foremost festival in India which signifies that movement where everything is moving like planets, humans, and other species to move in the future also. Here earth revolving is treated as the completion of one year so it is celebrated however it is also said that the harrowing winter started to end and a warm ray of sunshine hits the planet Earth in the northward movement so that is the reason it is also called Uttarayan. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Makar Sankranti Significance</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>You have seen our elders that they follow one ritual that to take a Ganga bath on Sankranti or wish to worship the Ganga or to chant the mantras while taking bath. Doing charity was the priority of elders as it was on 1st checklist as they believe that charity should be done once in a year to make us remember that we are just paying the rent to God.<br>The Makar Sakranti is the festival that marks the day where there is a movement in the zodiac sign like Sagittarius enters in the sign of Capricorn from the day as the Sun is moving towards south to north (Dakshinayan to Uttarayan) direction as now the days will get longer and the night will be shorter. As per the Panchang, the Capricorn’s sun is in the change so people will get to celebrate the festival for two days 14th and 15th January. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Time Difference of the Sun\'s zodiac change</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>As we very well know that every country has a different time zone and they have a unique calculation in their Panchang so in the year 2022 there are different views regarding the Makar Sankranti due to this there is a slight change in the position of the Sun. As per the Indian Calendar, there is a change of Sun in Capricorn from dated 14th January by the afternoon 2:30 PM however, as per the Hindu Panchang the zodiac change of the Sun will change by Night 8 PM on 14th of January so due to this sun will change to Capricorn so will be celebrating the festival on 15th of January, Saturday.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Why everything after Kharmas as per the Hindu Panchang</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>Kharmas is the month where no auspicious thing is mostly prohibited so Makar is considered to be the end of Kharmas and all the auspicious work will start as when the Sagittarius travels in Sun then there is a collision at that time. However, when the Sun hits the North direction so after that, every kind of auspicious works starts to take place for the new beginning like for marriage, home deities, and many more. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Harvest in Makar Sankranti</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>It is also known as the harvest festival so in Northside there is a huge celebration regarding this festival and it is the way of acknowledging thanks to all those who have assisted in making this harvest possible. So, in different regions it is celebrated as different names like in south it is celebrated as Pongal, the northeast side is said as Makar Sankranti, Westside it is treated as Uttarayan and in Northside is celebrated as Lohri.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><br><strong>First Ritual of Makar Sankranti</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>The first ritual is to take a Ganga bath as depicts that for a new beginning we must clean ourselves and the elders also state that Ganga takes all the impurities and provides goodness by generating better health. After that ritual one should donate sesame seeds and khichadi to the poor or the needy people as it clears the Shani dosha as Shani is the son of Lord Sun by offering water to the Sun after taking bath. The best part is that every year people from different regions celebrate the festival by eating different dishes like in North they will eat (sarso-da-saag with cornflour chapattis), in North-East and eastern region every family starts their day with eating curd and flattened rice (Chura) or khichdi, or anything made with sesame seeds or rice powder, the west part they will start will sesame seeds ladoos and in South, they will eat curd rice to start their day. The west of India (Gujarat) has a culture to have kite fighting ritual every year, and they organize competitions also in Runn of Kutch where people from different countries visit just to become a part of this celebration however after pandemic it is taken a step back. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/astrology-advice\">Astrology Advice</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Makar Sankranti the start of Fresh Beginnings', 'After the Lohri the most auspicious festival for Hindus is Makar Sankranti as in this festival it is said that after the Kharmas the festival is welcomed & all the auspicious work is done after that.', 'makar sankranti, Kites festival, Uttarayan, sankranti, sankrant, january festival, dahi chura, sesame seed, sessame, astrology advice, talk to astrologer', 1, 'makar-sankranti-the-start-of-fresh-beginnings', 'festivals', 'makar sankranti, Kites festival, Uttarayan, sankranti', '1641990488.jpg', 0, '2022-01-12 06:58:37', '2022-01-12 07:01:54'),
(56, 'Vastu tips for Work Space , Offices and Business', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Astrologykart.com, The success, and expansion of a company are directly linked to the construction of a positive, motivating, and enjoyable work environment. VastuShastra, an architectural science, aids in the development of a positive professional work culture for both management and staff, allowing an office space to flourish with success and profitability. Following Vastu principles in the construction and design of an office\'s interiors and exteriors will bring good luck and prosperity to the company. So, here are some Vastu office recommendations that will make your workplace a haven of happiness and growth. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>The office building\'s direction&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• The north, north-east, or north-west are desirable directions for office buildings since they provide luck and positivity to the company. The north is the direction of Kuber, the Lord of Wealth, and it improves the business financially. For a service industry-related workplace, the East orientation is ideal <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/astrology-advice\">Astrology Advice</a></strong>. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>The location of the office</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;• For success, the office should be located in a crowded area rather than a deserted one. It needs to be surrounded by moving traffic.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Plan for the office&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• SherMukhi plots are ideal for commercial buildings because their shape resembles that of a lion, which is a symbol of power, efficiency, and control. These plots are wide in the front and narrow in the back when facing north.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>The entrance to the office&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• The office\'s main entrance must face north or east without any obstructions. Things to stay away from The entrance door should never be on the side of an inner wall, as this will prevent beneficial energy from entering.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Reception&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• Astrologykart.com, The reception of any workplace, according to VastuShastra, represents the company\'s power and nature. As a result, it must exude great energy to visitors, clients, and even workers. The receptionist must sit with her back to the north or east. In the offices, the reception area must be built in an east or northeast direction. The corporate profile should be displayed on the south wall, and the reception counter should face the main entry door diagonally. Flowers can be displayed on the welcome desk to promote positivity. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Staircase&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• According to Vastu rules for offices, the best spot to build a staircase is in the south or southwest direction. The stairwells should be painted in light colors. Things to stay away from The staircase in the heart of the office should be avoided since it may result in financial losses. In offices, red and black stairwells should be avoided.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Workstations&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• Things like files, paperwork, and electronic appliances like computers must be stored on the left side of the table for north-facing workstations. The above-mentioned objects should be on the right-hand side of east-facing workstations. According to VastuShastra, workstations should be square or rectangular in design with four corners.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• <strong>Astrologykart.com</strong>, Things to avoid: Workstations or desks should never be L-shaped or any other irregular shape because this might lead to confusion and delays in work delivery. It is considered disrespectful to keep idols of Gods and Goddesses on your desk. Never eat food at your office or desk, as this is just for business purposes.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Owners\' rooms in the office&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• The office owners\' room should be in the southwest direction. They should always work with their backs to the north. The office owner\'s desk must be rectangular in design with four suitable corners. The owner\'s seat must always be backed by a solid concrete wall.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• Things to avoid: Temples or divine idols should not be kept behind the office owners\' seats <strong>chat with astrologers.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><strong>Employees\' workstation Employees\' workstations must face either north or east.&nbsp;</strong></li><li><strong>Department of Accounts</strong></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>In offices, the accounts department should be positioned in the north or east, as these directions are best for making monetary transactions. Furthermore, the Southwest or North of the cabinet is the finest spot to hold financial records. ϖ Department of marketing </li><li>Marketing and sales personnel should be stationed in the northwest corners of the office, facing north. This is a good path to take because it keeps people motivated. <strong><a href=\"