(101, 'Puja Vidhi for Durga Ashtami', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Durga Ashtami 2022: Masik Durgashtami is a one-of-a-kind Goddess Durga\'s festival that is observed nearly every month to get divine benefits. Witnessing the strength of NavaDurga, who is recognized as Hinduism\'s most ferocious Goddess, is considered a particularly auspicious religious practice. Masik Durgashtami is also known as Maas Durgashtami or Durga Ashtami (Monthly Durgashtami). <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong>, According to the Hindu calendar, it is celebrated just on the 8th day of Shukla Paksha, Ashtami Tithi. Every month, devotees of Mother Durga keep a traditional fast from morning until dusk and pray fervently. Maha Ashtami, which takes place in Ashwin month during the holy nine days of Shardiya Navratri festivities, is the most quintessential Ashtami of all Hindu festivals.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Vrat Vidhi Masik Durgashtami</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The lord of Ashtami Tithi, according to texts, is Shiva, who is also complementary to Durga\'s form of Durgesh. A demon named Durgam caused a disturbance throughout the three worlds, according to the Markandeya Purana. All the gods and goddesses became enraged as a result of his oppression, and Mother Durga was created from the might of Tridev, i.e. Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh. All the gods and goddesses are supposed to have petitioned the mother &amp; prayed to her to liberate her from the tyranny of the evil, after which the mother killed the demon, earning her the name Durgasaini. Although a Durgashtami occurs every month, the largest and most significant of them all is Durga Ashtami \'Mahashtami\', which occurs during Navratri. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer</a></strong>, it is believed that observing Durgashtami vrat with suitab