(137, 'Preparations for Holi 2022', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Holi, a prominent Hindu holiday, holds a great deal of spiritual importance. Holi is a Hindu social, religious, and cultural event that is widely observed. Holi ushers at the end of winter\'s dreary days and ushers in the joys of spring. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Colors, vitality, and mirth are also added to our lives when the seasons change. Let us keep prepared for the festivities by learning the date, time, and puja method of this great holiday as our relatives and friends prepare to enjoy it in a colourful and tasty fashion.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Date &amp; timing of Holi in 2022</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The final full moon day in the month of Phalguna is observed on the calendar as Holi (February - March). Holi will happen on Friday, March 18 in 2022. On March 17, 2022, at 01:29 p.m., the Purnima tithi begins and finishes at 12:46 p.m. on March 18, 2022.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>On the eve of Holi, there is a Holika Dahan celebration.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Holika Dahan is a major ceremony performed by all the homes in a village or town on the eve of Holi in a commonplace. Holika Dahan will take place in 2022 on Thursday, March 17th. The most appropriate Muhurat for Holika Dahan is for 1 hour and 10 minutes. It is extremely helpful to do the ritual exclusively within this time period. On Thursday, March 17, 2022, the Muhurat for Holika Dahan is between 9:20 and 10:31 p.m.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>Holika Dahan preparations should begin far ahead of time, preferably a few days before Holi, to ensure that everything is in order and there are no last-minute rushes or difficulties. Take a bath before Holika Dahan and bring the puja ingredients to Holika\'s location. Sit with your back to the north or east. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Create Prahlad and Holika idols. The idol of Prahlad is made of non-flammable material, while the idol of Holika is composed of combustible material, according to legend. The idols are put inside the pyre, which is surrounded by firewood and other burning elements.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Offer Lord Narasimha prayers and puja and go around the pyre seven times during Holika Dahan. Throw flowers, cotton, jaggery, moong, turmeric, coconut, gulal, batasha, seven types of cereals, and other crops into the fire as offerings while circumambulating the blazing pyre. Pray for your family, friends, and the entire globe. Sing and dance joyfully around the fire, accompanied by traditional Holika Dahan music. Symbolically, burn your undesirable traits in the Holika Dahan fire, and your prayers will be miraculously realized at this period, according to popular belief.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Holi festivities and puja</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Holi Puja may be performed on Friday, March 18, 2022, and all of the festivities can take place during the Purnima tithi, which ends at 12:46 p.m.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Holi puja is performed in a variety of ways, depending on the customs. The most typical custom is to place Radha and Krishna\'s idols on an altar, dress them up in beautiful robes and jewellery, and offer puja and a variety of cuisines as offerings. The entire family is gathered around the altar, chanting Krishna and Radha chants and praying for the family\'s well-being. Sweets and other eatables are handed to the assembled members at the conclusion of the puja.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>During Holi, people spray colours and coloured water on each other in a festival of colours. Buy only eco-friendly colours to guarantee that the colours you spray are not damaging. Share the pleasure of Holi with everyone and pray for global peace, prosperity, and blessings. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, The event is regarded as the ideal day to forget all their grievances and just forget all the misfortunes of the past so that you may enjoy every moment of it.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Preparations for Holi 2022', 'Preparations for Holi 2022 is started and everyone has bought their new clothes, eating gujiyas, celebrating Holi with organic colours & welcoming their guests.', 'Preparations for Holi 2022, Holi 2022, Holika Dahan 2022, happy holi 2022, Happy Holika Dahan 2022, holika dahan wishes,  happy holi 2022 images, Choti Holi 2022,  Happy Holi 2022 Wishes, holi images', 1, 'preparations-for-holi-2022', 'festivals', 'Holi 2022, Holika Dahan 2022, happy holi 2022, Happy Holika Dahan 2022', '1647500461.jpg', 0, '2022-03-17 01:32:09', '2022-03-17 01:45:39'),
(138, 'The Best Updesha of Gautam Buddha', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mahatma Buddha\'s Personality - Around 563 BC, Mahatma Buddha was born in the Lumbini jungle near Kapilvastu. Shuddhodana, his father, was the Shakya Republic of Kapilavastu\'s ruler. Mayadevi was his mother\'s name. Siddhartha was Mahatma Buddha\'s childhood name. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Siddhartha has been showing signs of intellect and compassion since he was a toddler. The king married his son to Yashodhara, the lovely and virtuous daughter of a Shakya chieftain since he found his son uninterested in worldliness. Rahul, his son, was also born to him.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p> \"<strong>Today another link has been connected to the chain of my relationship</strong>,\" Siddhartha said loudly upon his birth. So he went to the jungle with his charioteer Chandak one night, leaving his wife and newborn infant in a drowsy condition and Rajaprasad behind. Mahabhinishkraman is the name of this event. He was around 30 years old at the time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In pursuit of truth - After leaving home, he began roaming about looking for answers. He first adopted the austere brahmins\' discipleship, studying the texts and philosophy, but this did not offer him peace. He performed a lot of penance as well, but he didn\'t get any understanding from it. Finally, he sat down under a peepal tree in Gaya, on the banks of the river Nairanjana. When the samadhi ended, a light emerged in his heart, and he discovered a way to end human misery. Since then, Siddhartha has been referred to as \'Buddha,\' and the tree has been dubbed the Bodhi tree.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Buddha resolved to show the world the way of knowledge after preaching-action-enlightenment. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk o Astrologer Online</a></strong>, First, he travelled to Sarnath, in modern-day Varanasi, where he reconnected with his former five buddies who had abandoned him. He made the five friends his followers by preaching to them in Sarnath for the first time. Dharmachakra Pravartan is the name given to this doctrine, and these five pupils are known as \"Panchvargiya.\"</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mahaparinirvana - For forty-five years, Buddha preached nirvana from the palaces of India to the huts of India, and he died in 483 BC while preaching in Kushinagar. \'<strong>Mahaparinirvana</strong>\' is the name given to this phenomenon. He was 80 years of age at that point.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Mahatma Buddha\'s Teachings</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mahatma Buddha\'s teachings are straightforward and practical. He used to deliver his sermons in plain English.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mahatma Buddha\'s Teachings: Mahatma Buddha\'s teachings are straightforward and practical. He used to deliver his sermons in plain English. Mahatma Buddha\'s moral and philosophical teachings</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>1. What were Gautam Buddha\'s moral paths?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The <strong>\'Four Arya Truths</strong>,\' as taught by Gautam Buddha, are extremely important. Coming up next are the four honorable bits of insight:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(a) Sorrow - The world is a sad place.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Life is terrible because of old age, sickness, and death, because of the separation from one\'s beloved and the combination of the unpleasant, the incompleteness of one\'s wishes and desires, and because of the separation of one\'s beloved and the combination of the unpleasant. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, This is a sad situation that affects everyone.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(b) Sorrow-community-</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Gautam Buddha referred to it as the \"<strong>community of sorrow</strong>,\" or \"<strong>cause</strong>.\" He said that desire is the basis of sadness. Trishna is the Sanskrit word for devotion to worldly possessions and sensual pleasures. Increased desire leads to hubris, strife, hatred, and misery, among other things.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(c) Suffering-</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>He also mentioned the possibility of imprisonment. The abolition of desire puts a stop to birth, death, and all of life\'s tragedies. When all of a person\'s wants are satisfied, he or she achieves Nirvana and is free of sadness.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(d) The cessation of sorrow is in this world-</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Buddha Ji also explained the path to nirvana or the cessation of suffering. To put a stop to suffering, he devised the <strong>\'Ashtangaik Path</strong>,\' which consists of eight standards of behaviour. The following are the details:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(1) (</strong><strong>सम्यक</strong><strong> </strong><strong>दृष्टि</strong><strong>) </strong>Right perspective</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(2) (</strong><strong>सम्यक्</strong><strong> </strong><strong>संकल्प</strong><strong>) </strong>Enough resolution</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(3) (</strong><strong>सम्यक्</strong><strong> </strong><strong>संकल्प</strong><strong>) </strong>Proper speech</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(4) (</strong><strong>सम्यकर्म</strong><strong>) </strong>Right action</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(5) (</strong><strong>सम्यक</strong><strong> </strong><strong>जीविका</strong><strong>) </strong>Right livelihood</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(6) (सम्यक उद्योग) </strong>Right industry</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(7) (</strong><strong>सम्यक्</strong><strong> </strong><strong>स्मृति</strong><strong>) </strong>Right memory</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>(8) (</strong><strong>सम्यक्</strong><strong> </strong><strong>समाधि</strong><strong>) </strong>Right Memorial.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'The Best Updesha of Gautam Buddha', 'Here are some of the Best Updesha of Gautam Buddha that you can initiate in your life to have better well-being and you can take learnings from that.', 'Updesha of Gautam Buddha,  Gautam Budhha, Mythology, Budha, Gautam buddha ke updesh, Learnings of Gautam Buddha', 1, 'the-best-updesha-of-gautam-buddha', 'mythological-tales', 'Updesha of Gautam Buddha,  Gautam Budhha, Mythology, Budha', '1647848617.jpg', 0, '2022-03-21 02:13:47', '2022-03-21 02:18:33'),
