(140, 'Shaheed Diwas 2022: Why Bhagat Singh, Sukhdev, and Rajguru sacrificed their life for the country on 23 March 1931?', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Shaheed Diwas:</strong> In 1947, India earned freedom from the British after 200 years of servitude. Was this liberation, though, so simple? Certainly not. India had to make not one, not two, but lakhs of sacrifices as the price of independence. To honor their sacrifices and heroism, India commemorates Martyr\'s Day. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, People talk about the wonderful tales of such young combatants who battled with heroism and retell the tales of their valor every year on March 23rd.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Following Lala Lajpat Rai\'s assassination, Bhagat Singh, Rajguru, Sukhdev, Azad, and others seized the lead in the fight for freedom. On April 8, 1929, he tossed explosives in the Central Assembly in protest of the Public Safety and Trade Distributor Bill, raising his voice against British control.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhagat Singh, Rajguru, and Sukhdev were arrested and accused of murder after raising shouts of \'Inquilab Zindabad.\' On the accusation of murder, he was hung in Lahore Jail on March 23, 1931. Sukhdev and Rajguru, along with Bhagat Singh, had given their lives that night for the liberation of their nation. On the banks of the Sutlej River, his death rituals were administered. Shaheedi Mela, or Martyrdom Mela, is still celebrated in Hussainiwala, where he was born, or on the Indo-Pak border.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On allegations of Lahore Conspiracy, he was executed by the British government. Bhagat Singh was just 23 years of age at that point. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, He gave his life for the independence of Mother India when