(147, 'Gangaur Puja: Why it is celebrated?', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In India, the Gangaur festival was also celebrated with zeal. Women worshipped Lord Shiva and Parvati at temples around the city and in rural regions<strong>.<a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\"> Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Women have been spotted dressing up and coming to the temples to worship Gangaur in the morning.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Women, in particular, honor Lord Shankar by using cosmetics on Gangaur day. While fasting, he prays for the happiness and success of the family in addition to the husband\'s long life. Unmarried females also worship Lord Shiva on Gangaur by fasting and praying for a decent spouse. Temples in various parts of the country were used for worship. Shiva Parvati was also established and worshipped in the parks.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Women also performed traditional songs like \"Gor Gomti, Isar Puja Parvati\" at this time. In addition, numerous female groups held cultural events to commemorate the Gangaur holiday socially. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, The women crafted jaggery and flour jewelry for the Lord. Women presented Goddess Parvati with suhaag material on this occasion. The ladies made special delicacies in their houses.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On the third day of Shukla Paksha in Chaitra month, the Gangaur festival is held. This event is mostly observed in the state of Rajasthan. This event, by the way, begins on the second day of Holi. For the next sixteen days, it is commemorated. And it is completed on Chaitra Shukla\'s Tritiya. Married ladies fast on this day in order for their husbands to live a long and happy life. Saubhagya Tritiya is another name for Gangaur Teej.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Unmarried and freshly married ladies offer water to the adored Gangaur in a river, pond, or lake a day before Gangaur Teej. The second day begins in the evening and ends in the morning. Unmarried ladies maintain Gangaur\'s Vakra in the hopes of finding the perfect mate. And married women observe a fast with rituals on this day in order to obtain affection from their husbands.<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://vdo.ai/?utm_medium=video&amp;utm_term=abplive.com&amp;utm_source=vdoai_logo\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Isar-Gaur is worshipped </strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lord Shiva and Mata Gauri, also known as Isar Dev, are worshipped on this day. Lord Shiva and Mata Gauri are sculpted from pure, clean clay on the day of the Gangaur fast. They are then lavishly adorned and ritualistically worshipped.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Gangaur Teej Worship Method</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lord Shiva and Mother Parvati bestowed good fortune on all living things on the day of Gangaur Teej. Maa Parvati is therefore built with clay and worshipped on this day, before fasting. Make a square altar 24 fingers wide by 24 fingers long in a sacred chamber of the house to establish Gauri of clay. Turmeric, sandalwood, camphor, saffron, and other spices are used throughout the square.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Make Maa Gauri out of the sand and then gift honey-related products such as glass bangles, Mahavar, vermilion, roli, henna, tika, bindi, comb, mirror, kajal, and so on.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The quick narrative of Gauri Ji is told during worship time. Akshat, sandalwood, and incense lamp are used to glorify Mother. Maa Parvati is provided suhaag articles. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\"><strong>Chat</strong> <strong>with Astrologer Online</strong></a>, Women fulfill their requests with vermilion presented to the mother after hearing the narrative. In the afternoon, Gangaur is worshipped. Food is only consumed once a day after that and the fast is broken. Offerings of Gangaur are said to be forbidden for males.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Gangaur Puja: Why it is celebrated?', 'Gangaur Puja: Why it is celebrated and what are the factors that every married couple celebrates this festival on a large scale in Rajasthan. Know more...', 'Gangaur 2022,Gangaur, Saubhagya Teej, Rituals and Celebrations, Gauri Tritiya, Chaitra Navratri, Gangaur festival, Gangaur Puja, shiva, parvati, shiva parvati, Gangaur Ki Katha, story of gangaur, devotional story', 1, 'gangaur-puja-why-it-is-celebrated', 'festivals', 'Gangaur 2022, Gangaur Puja,  Saubhagya Teej, Rituals and Celebrations', '1649070334.jpg', 0, '2022-04-04 05:45:21', '2022-04-04 06:33:04'),
(148, 'When is Hanuman Jayanti?', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Hanuman Jayanti 2022: </strong>Hanuman Jayanti will be observed on the full moon day of Chaitra month, according to the Panchang. The full moon in Shukla Paksha of Chaitra month falls on April 16th this year.<a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\"> <strong>Astrology Advice Online</strong></a>, This day is known as Hanuman Jayanti. The Navratri festival (Navratri 2022) is now taking place. On April 10th, Ram Navami (ram Navami Navratri 2022) is observed. Following that, the Hanuman Jayanti celebration will be observed.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>When is Hanuman Ji\'s birthday in 2022?</strong><br>It is customary to celebrate the full moon day of Chaitra Shukla as Hanuman Ji\'s birthday. The day of Hanuman Jayanti is regarded as the most auspicious for obtaining the blessings of Hanuman Ji. Religious events are held around the country on this day. On this day, Hanuman worshippers fast and worship Hanuman Ji.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Date and Muhurta for Hanuman Jayanti in 2022 (Hanuman Jayanti 2022 in India)</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>According to the Panchang, the Chaitra month\'s full moon will begin on Saturday, April 16, at 02:25 a.m. On this day, at 12.24 p.m., the Purnima Tithi comes to a close. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\"><strong>Talk to</strong> <strong>Astrologer Online</strong></a>, The full moon date is received on 16 April at sunrise, hence Hanuman Jayanti will be observed on that day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>On Hanuman Jayanti, auspicious yoga is practiced.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Ravi Yoga is being established this year on Hanuman Jayanti, according to Panchang calculations. This yoga is said to be the finest for finishing any task in the scriptures. Because of the particular impact of the Sun, Ravi-Yoga is regarded to be an effective yoga. This is why, because this yoga is full of the Sun\'s divine force, the odds of failure in the task done in this yoga are quite low. According to the Panchang, Hasta Nakshatra is up till 08:40 in the morning on this day, April 16. The Chitra Nakshatra will begin after that. The Moon will be transiting Virgo on this day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Worship method on Hanuman Jayanti</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>At morning, Hanuman ji was born. As a result, worshipping at Brahmamuhurta on Hanuman Jayanti is considered beneficial. On this day, Hanuman Ji\'s treasures should be presented. On this day, the Hanuman Chalisa, Sundarkand, and Hanuman Aarti should be performed.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>It is a religious concept that worshipping Bajrangbali by law on Hanuman Jayanti brings about desired consequences, however, bear in mind that one must also worship Ram Darbar when worshipping Hanuman Ji. Because it is considered that Hanuman Ji\'s worship would be incomplete without Ram Ji\'s devotion and that the rewards of worship would not be obtained.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Hanuman Ji\'s birth tale is as follows:</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When Monarch Dasharatha, the king of Ayodhya, conducted Putreshti Havan, he gave kheer to his three queens as prasad, according to mythology. A bit of that kheer was carried away by a crow and arrived at Mata Anjana Shiva\'s seat of penance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mother Anjana took the kheer as Shiva\'s prasad when she got it. This incidence was made possible by Lord Shiva and Pawan Dev. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Hanuman Ji was born after accepting that prasad. Lord Shiva\'s 11th Rudravatar, Hanuman Ji, is revered.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Hanuman ji is also known as Anjaneya because of his mother Anjana, Kesarinandan because of his father Vanararaj Kesari, and Pawanputra, Bajrangbali, Hanuman because of Pawan Dev\'s collaboration.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'When is Hanuman Jayanti?', 'When is Hanuman Jayanti 2022? Know the date and time of Puja and why it is being celebrated in India. Know the story of the devotee of Shree Ram- Hanuman Ji', 'hanuman jayanti 2022, when is hanuman jayanti 2022, Hanuman ji,Hanuman Puja,Hanuman Jayanti 2022, April 2022, Hanuman Jayanti 2022, Hanuman Jayanti 2022 Date, Hanuman Janm Katha', 1, 'when-is-hanuman-jayanti', 'festivals', 'hanuman jayanti 2022, when is hanuman jayanti 2022, Hanuman ji,Hanuman Puja', '1649248052.jpg', 0, '2022-04-06 07:02:18', '2022-04-06 07:02:18'),
(149, 'World Health day 2022', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The 7th of April is a significant day in the realm of health. Every year on April 7th, World Health Day is commemorated. The corona pandemic has been spreading internationally in recent years. The disease spread to nearly every country on the planet. In this circumstance, the World Health Organization has attempted to provide health services to the entire world at every level. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Better health facilities should be available everywhere, and illness may be avoided.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Similarly, practically all nations should be disease-free and have no scarcity of health-care services; all of this is a major reason for commemorating World Health Day. But have you ever wondered why Health Day is only observed on April 7th? What is the meaning of World Health Day and what is its history? Tell us why World Health Day is celebrated, as well as the subject and manner for this year.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What is the significance of April 7th being Health Day?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In fact, the World Health Organization was founded on April 7th. As a result, World Health Day began on the anniversary of the World Health Organization\'s founding. For the first time in 1950, World Health Day was observed by all WHO member nations. Following that, as more nations joined the WHO, April became International Health Day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>World Health Day: A Brief History</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In the year 1948, the World Health Organization (WHO) was formed. It was chosen to commemorate World Health Day two years later, in the year 1950. The World Health Organization (WHO) took the lead in establishing this day as a worldwide commemoration. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\"> <strong>Talk to Astrologer Online</strong></a>, The commemoration of World Health Day officially began at that point.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The goal of World Health Day</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The goal of Globe Health Day is to raise awareness about the need for having the same health facilities in all nations throughout the world, refute health myths, and reflect on and act on global health issues. On this day, public awareness initiatives on health services, facilities, and care are held.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The work of the World Health Organization</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The World Health Organization commemorates World Health Day. This organization works to improve people\'s health all across the world. WHO collaborates with the United Nations, agencies, national health administrations, professional associations, and other organizations in the field of health. Aids in the strengthening of health services at the request of the country\'s governments. Encourages the participation of professional organizations and specialists.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>World Health Day Theme of the year 2022</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>\'Our planet, our health\' is the topic for World Health Day 2022 this year. The focus of this year\'s topic is on the health of every human being on our planet. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, On the occasion of World Health Day, India is holding a \'Yoga Amrit Mahotsav,\' which is coordinated by the Ministry of AYUSH. \'Building a Fair, Healthy World\' was the theme of World Health Day 2021.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'World Health Day 2022', 'World Health day 2022 is celebrated on the 7th of April. So, what is the significance of celebrating this day, and what is the connection with WHO in this?', 'World Health Day, World Health Day 2022, 2022 World health day, WHO, World Health Organization, 7th of April. World Health Day', 1, 'world-health-day-2022', 'current-affairs', 'World Health Day, World Health Day 2022, 2022 World health day, WHO', '1649329367.jpg', 0, '2022-04-07 05:32:59', '2022-04-09 03:07:23'),
(150, 'Celebrating Durga Ashtami 2022 of this Chaitra Navratri', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Chaitra Navratri, Durga Ashtami 2022:</strong> Today is Chaitra Navratri\'s Ashtami. The adoration of Maa Durga in nine forms is regarded as highly significant during Navratri. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Maa Mahagauri, the eighth form of Goddess Durga, is celebrated on the eighth day of the Shukla Paksha of the Chaitra month. It is a religious belief that by worshipping Maa Mahagauri with a genuine heart on Ashtami Tithi, all the devotees\' requests are granted.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Maa Mahagauri is known as Mamta\'s idol. Worshiping Maa Mahagauri, according to astrological beliefs, reduces Rahu\'s negative effects. In the holy days of Navratri, Ashtami Tithi holds particular importance. Please let us know when the Ashtami day of Chaitra Navratri is this year and how to worship Goddess Durga\'s eighth avatar on this day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Date &amp; Time of Chaitra Navratri 2022 Ashtami</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Ashtami is on April 9th this year. According to the Panchang, Ashtami Tithi begins at 11.05 p.m. on the night of April 8th. It will also expire during the late night of April 9 at 1:23 p.m. The Navami date will then begin.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Puja Method for Durga shtami 2022</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>To get the blessings of Goddess Durga in her eighth form, Maa Maha Gauri, on this day, first place an idol or portrait of Maha Gauri on a wooden pillar or at a temple. Then, place a white cloth on the pole and set the Maha Gauri Yantra on top of it to complete the yantra. Then, grab some flowers and reflect on the mother. <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\"><strong>Chat with Astrologer</strong> <strong>Online</strong></a>, Now, light a lamp in front of the mother\'s idol and present her fruits, flowers, naivedya, and so on, as well as to conduct the mother goddess aarti.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Maha Ashtami Puja Significance </strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Maa Mahagauri is worshipped in order to eliminate impediments to marriage. It is stated that worshipping Mahagaurikeeps married life happy. Along with this, the family strife comes to an end. Mata Sita is said to have adored Goddess Mahagauri just for the sake of obtaining Shri Ram.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Importance of Worshipping a Girl </strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Worshiping a female on Ashtami during Navratri is seen to be the most auspicious. Goddess Durga is said to be pleased with the adoration of females during Navratri and to bestow pleasure and prosperity to the followers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Girl Worship Method</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Kanya Puja is conducted on the day of Maha Ashtami or Navami during Navratri. A languria, also known as a \"bhairava\" (young boy), is served puri, pudding, gram curry, and other foods with females aged 2 to 10 years. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Following that, their blessings are obtained by applying tilak to the females, tying Mauli in their hands, and bestowing gifts-Dakshina, among other things.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Celebrating Durga Ashtami 2022 of this Chaitra Navratri', 'Celebrating Durga Ashtami 2022 of this Chaitra Navratri. As you need to know the Importance of Kanya Pujan and why Chaitra Navratri Durga Puja is so special?', '