(151, 'Shiv Kumar Subramaniam, a veteran actor, died, saying goodbye to the world barely two months after his son died.', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Shiv Kumar Subramaniam, a well-known Bollywood actor, and screenwriter died on Monday, April 11th, in the early hours of the morning. The new week began with disappointing news for the film industry. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>,  Shiv Kumar Subramaniam, a well-known Bollywood actor, and screenwriter died late last night (Shiv Kumar Subramaniam death). The whole film business was in grief as soon as the news of the actor\'s death became public. The cause of Shiv Kumar\'s death is unknown at this time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bina Sarwar took to Twitter to express her sadness at the news. \"Very terrible news,\' he wrote. He died barely two months after his son Jahan died. Jahan, his son, suffered a brain tumor. He died before reaching the age of sixteen. According to the source, Subramaniam\'s last rites would be held on Monday, April 11, at 11 a.m. at the Mokshadham Hindu Crematorium.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Shiv Kumar Subramaniam was last seen in the film \"Meenakshi Sundareswarar\" last year. Sanya Malhotra played the lead in this flick. Aside from that, the actor has acted in many films and television series. He\'s also authored screenplays for a few movies. The actor penned the screenplays for the films Parinda\' by Vidhu Vinod Chopra and \'Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi\' by Sudhir Mishra.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Shiv Kumar Subramaniam began his career in cinema in 1989, when he wrote the script for Vidhu Vinod Chopra\'s Parinda. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Other notable films he has written include \"1942: A Love Story, Is Raat Ki Subah Nahin, Arjun Pandit, Chameli, Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi, and Teen Patti\". Subramaniam received Filmfare awards for Best Story and Best Screenplay for his work on \"Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi\" and \"Parinda\".</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>While the reason for Shiv Subramaniam\'s death is unknown, it was filmmaker Hansal Mehta who announced Shiv Subramaniam\'s departure on his social media page. The announcement disclosed the specifics of the late actor\'s burial, which will take place today in Mumbai. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The following is Hansal Mehta\'s statement</strong>:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:html -->\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Terrible news to wake up to. Shiv Subramaniam gone. Heartbreaking.</p>&mdash; Hansal Mehta (@mehtahansal) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mehtahansal/status/1513312153285144577?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 11, 2022</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\r\n<!-- /wp:html -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Many more actors also tweeted such as:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Gulshan Devaiah and Manoj Bajpayee</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:html -->\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Rest in Peace Shiv 🙏 <a href=\"https://t.co/BGQoPPSj5y\">pic.twitter.com/BGQoPPSj5y</a></p>&mdash; Gulshan Devaiah (@gulshandevaiah) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gulshandevaiah/status/1513350679393308676?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 11, 2022</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\r\n<!-- /wp:html -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:html -->\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Rest in peace Shiv!! 🙏 <br>Such a tragic news one woke up to! <br>Condolences to the family &amp; friends!! <a href=\"https://t.co/tm2