(159, 'Remembering Rabindranath Tagore, his timeless wisdom, and why it is still important today', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Last year, when delivering the Union Budget, Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman used Nobel laureate Rabindranath Tagore to draw a link with the country\'s predicament in the aftermath of the COVID-19 epidemic. She selected the following statement to emphasize the advent of a new age, “where India is well-poised to be the country of hope and promise.\"</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>At the 76th United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) in September 2021, Prime Minister Narendra Modi closed his address with the aforementioned quotation from the Nobel winner. The phrases mean \"one should go fearlessly in the route of good action and conquer all shortcomings and uncertainties in the endeavor.\" PM Modi stated that the words applied to all nations.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>BUT WHY ARE WE DISCUSSING ABOUT RABINDRANATH TAGORE?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On the 7th of May we Rabindranath Tagore Jayanti to gratitude the Nobel prize winner who tried to represent his country in the world by just his writings. Rabindranath Tagore was the first non-European and Indian lyricist to be awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1913. On the 161st anniversary of his birth, here\'s a look at the Nobel laureate\'s life and times.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>For any kind of career related problems you can <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Rabindranath Tagore was a Bengali polymath who worked as a poet, painter, writer, musician, dramatist, philosopher, and social reformer. His works had a significant impact on Bengali literature, music, and Indian art forms. In 1913, he became the first non-European and Indian lyricist to receive the Nobel Prize in Literature. On the 161st anniversary of his birth, here\'s a look back at the Nobel laureate\'s life and times.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Tagore, who was born Rabindranath Thakur on May 7, 1861, began composing poems at the age of eight. He went on to publish his first poetry under the pen name Bhanusiha (meaning Sun Lion). His family was in the vanguard of the Bengal Renaissance, and he had 12 siblings. Tagore is the titular character in Valmiki Pratibha (1881), with his niece Indira Devi as the goddess Lakshmi.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Tagore and his father left Calcutta in 1873 to travel to India. Before arriving in Dalhousie, they paid visits to the Santiniketan estate and Amritsar. Tagore enrolled in a public school in Brighton, East Sussex, England in 1878 because his father intended him to become a barrister.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In 1880, he returned to Bengal without a degree and three years later married Mrinalini Devi, a 10-year-old girl. They shared five children. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Tagore relocated to Santiniketan in 1901 and established an ashram, where his father, wife, and two children died. Tagore was awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature in November 1913 for his translated work centered on the 1912 Gitanjali: Song Offerings.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>King George V knighted Tagore in the 1915 Birthday Honours, but he renounced it following the 1919 Jallianwala Bagh massacre. He has visited the world extensively and has met celebrities like Albert Einstein. He visited Shanghai in 1924 and is said to have donated a Rs 500 gift in a fundraising effort during the Japan-China conflict. CNBCTV18.com was unable to confirm the source of this information.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On August 7, 1941, he died at the age of 80. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Tagore has eight museums named after him, three of them are in India and five in Bangladesh. Politicians, educators, and leaders have often sought inspiration from Rabindranath Tagore\'s statements.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Remembering Rabindranath Tagore, his timeless wisdom, and why it is still important today', 'Remembering Rabindranath Tagore, his timeless wisdom, and why it is still important today. Why his writings are still relevant. Know more.', 'Rabindranath Tagore, Rabindranath Thakur, happy Rabindranath Tagore jayanti, poem of Rabindranath Tagore in Bengali, Rabindranath Tagore Nobel Prize, Rabindranath Tagore jayanti 2022, Rabindranath Tagore birthday', 1, 'remembering-rabindranath-tagore-his-timeless-wisdom-and-why-it-is-still-important-today', 'current-affairs', 'Rabindranath Tagore, Rabindranath Thakur, Rabindranath Tagore jayanti 2022, Rabindranath Tagore birthday', '1651917241.jpg', 0, '2022-05-07 04:26:59', '2022-05-07 04:26:59'),
(160, 'Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022: Remembering Events of Maharana Pratap\'s life.', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Maharana Pratap was a well-liked Rajput ruler of Mewar. He was recognized for his bravery and power. Maharana Pratap was Mewar\'s 13th king, and his birthday is commemorated every year on May 9. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, The birth anniversary of Maharana Pratap happens on Tritiya Tithi of Shukla Paksha of Jyeshtha, according to the Hindu calendar. Let us know about some noteworthy events in his life on Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022 by writing an article.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Maharana Pratap is remembered as our country\'s first liberation warrior. He is famous for his bravery in the face of Akbar\'s disobedience, as well as his loyal horse Chetak. At a period when others acknowledged Akbar\'s rule, the Maharana battled heroically against the Mughal Empire. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Jayanti is commemorated today in his honor.</strong><br>Maharana Pratap was the most skilled warrior of his siblings. He had devoted his life to the service of his motherland\'s defense. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Maharana Pratap\'s military opposition to the Mughal Empire\'s expansionism, as well as the battle of Haldighati, Dewar, are regarded as crucial.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br><strong>Things relating to Maharana Pratap\'s life are unique</strong><br>Maharana Pratap was born in a Rajput household on May 9, 1540, and his father, Udai Singh, was the founder of Udaipur. Maharana Pratap is well-known for his struggle to protect from the Mughal Empire spreading in India. The Battle of Haldighati was a groundbreaking fight against the Mughals in which the Maharana played a key role. He had the distinction of having defeated the powerful Mughal king Akbar three times.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When all of the Rajput chiefs surrendered in dread of the Mughals, Maharana Pratap remained alone against the Mughals. His bodily structure was drastically different. He was a 7-foot-5-inch guy who could effortlessly carry a sword weighing 104 kg and armor weighing 72 kg.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Despite being defeated in the battle of Haldighati, Maharana Pratap refused to surrender.  <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\"><strong>Chat with Astrologer Online</strong>,</a> Maharana Pratap reclaimed the regions taken by the Mughals. As a result, many people regard Maharana Pratap to be the first independent warrior. The people of Rajasthan and Himachal Pradesh hold numerous festivities to commemorate Maharana Pratap\'s birthday.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022: Remembering Events of Maharana Pratap\'s life.', 'Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022: Remembering Events of Maharana Pratap\'s life.  Noteworthy events in his life on Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022 on his birthday.', 'Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022,  maharana pratap, story of maharana pratap, maharana pratap life, maharana pratap jayanti, maharana pratap images, maharana pratap war, battle of haldighati', 1, 'maharana-pratap-jayanti-2022-remembering-events-of-maharana-prataps-life', 'current-affairs', 'Maharana Pratap Jayanti 2022,  maharana pratap, story of maharana pratap, maharana pratap life', '1652097858.jpg', 0, '2022-05-09 06:37:08', '2022-05-09 06:37:08'),
