(162, 'Vat Savitri Muharata 2022', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In Hinduism, married women follow many fasts for the long life and happiness of their husbands. The Vat Savitri fast is one of these fasts. This fast is held every year on the new moon day of the Jyeshtha month.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On this day, married ladies observe the law and pray to Lord Vishnu, Goddess Lakshmi, and the Banyan tree (Vat) for their husband\'s long life. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, She also prays for the long life of her spouse by circumambulating the banyan tree.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The Vat Savitri Vrat for the year 2022 will be observed on Monday, May 30, 2022, according to the Panchang. Somvati Amavasya falls on this day as well, making it the last Somvati Amavasya of the year.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Every year during the new moon of Jyeshtha month, the Vat Savitri fast is celebrated in North India. In Maharashtra, Gujarat, and South India, the Vat Savitri fast is observed on Jyeshtha Shukla Purnima. This year, several fortuitous coincidences occur during the Vat Savitri fast. This year\'s Vat Savitri Vrat will take place on May 30, 2022. Married couples commemorate Vat Savitri Vrat for the long life and prosperity of their spouses. Vat, or the Banyan tree, is revered during the Vat Savitri fast.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What is occurring on the day of Vat Savitri fasting-</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>This year, an auspicious coincidence of Shani Jayanti and Somvati Amavasya is taking place on the day of Vat Savitri Vrat. Amavasya on Monday is known as Somvati Amavasya. This will be the year\'s final Somvati Amavasya. The Somvati Amavasya coincidence will now take place in 2023. <strong><a href=\"https://