(163, 'Know about the Ganga Dussehra', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Let us tell you that in Hinduism, the Ganga is revered. All faults are claimed to be washed away when a person bathes in the Ganges River, and the person is blessed by God\'s limitless grace. Aside from that, Hinduism holds Gangajal in high regard. Gangajal is also utilized in ceremonies and auspicious activities. Let us assure you that no auspicious task is complete without Gangajal. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Ganga Dussehra commemorates Mother Ganga\'s arrival on Earth. On this day, everyone bathes in the sacred Ganges water to wash away their sins. Also, contemplate Mother Ganga. On the other hand, after washing, the person receives several benefits such as donating and so on.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Allow me to explain the significance of the Hindu festival of Ganga Dussehra. On Thursday, June 9th, 2022, this auspicious day will be remembered. Individuals also bathe in the Ganges on this day to wash away their sins. Let us notify you that Mother Ganga is claimed to have dropped on the earth on this day, which is why Ganga Dussehra is so widely observed. What is the significance of Ganga Dussehra, and when will it take place in 2022?</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Ganga Dussehra\'s Significance</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhagirath, according to legend, brought the Ganges to earth to save his forefathers\' souls. Ganga is also known as Bhagirathi for this reason. After hearing the velocity and power of Mother Ganga, it is thought that Markandeya Rishi\'s stubbornness was dissolved. Mother Ganga was thus honored by Markandeya sage. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, At the same moment, the sage released Mother Ganga by pushing the right toe of his foot on the dirt for the good of the people. Let us tell you that in Ganga Dussehra, the number 10 is extremely significant.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Dussehra in the Ganges</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Let us remind you that the tenth day of Shukla Paksha in the Jyeshtha month begins at 8.21 a.m. on June 9th and ends at 7.25 p.m. on June 10th. Hasta Nakshatra and Vyatipat Yoga will be established at the same time. In addition, there are several benefits to bathing and giving in this yoga. Those who conduct charitable activity during this period, on the other hand, will have all of their sins washed away. Mother Ganga has favoured her.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The significance of swimming in the Ganges during Ganga Dussehra</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Let us explain that on the day of Ganga Dussehra, people go from all over the world to bathe in the Ganges River. It is thought that the water of the Ganges is extremely sacred and that anyone who bathes in it on this day will have all of his sins washed away. Along with this, his redemption pathways are also opened, which is why people bathe in the Ganges River during Dussehra. Let us explain why the number 10 is so significant in Ganga Dussehra.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On the day of Dussehra, it is said that taking ten dips in the Ganges offers immense advantages. In addition, ten attitudes are broken on Dussehra day. Ten sorts of sins are said to be eliminated by bathing in the Mokshadayini Maa Ganga.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>One gets freedom from these sins by bathing in the Ganges</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The day of Ganga Dussehra is considered to be the day of Ganga Ji. Also, by taking bath in the Ganges and worshipping the Ganges on this holy day, the person gets freedom from 10 types of sins. Out of these 10 types of sins, three types of physical sins and four types of sins committed by speech, three types of mental sins get washed away.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What to contribute and why is charity important</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On the day of Ganga Dussehra, just as bathing in the Ganges River is regarded as extremely essential, so is conducting charitable work. On the day of Ganga Dussehra, it is stated that whoever performs charitable activity receives the blessings of Mother Ganga and has all of his difficulties eliminated.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Forth, Ganga Dussehra, bathing, charity, chanting, austerity, fasting, and other rituals are all considered very important. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, Shivling should also be worshipped with ten various perfumes, flowers, incense, lamps, naivedya, and fruits, among other things, after bathing in ten different ways on Dussehra. Make a special effort on this day to ensure that anything you give is a multiple of 10.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>During Ganga Puja, the number of devotional objects should also be ten. This has a positive outcome, as all of the difficulties in the person\'s life are resolved.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Tell us that donating stuff on Ganga Dussehra assures success.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• You may help people in need by donating food and fruits.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• Giving someone a pitcher full of water on Dussehra gives them good fortune.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• It is auspicious to give to those who are in need.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• Items such as clothing, shoes, and slippers can also be donated.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>• It is advantageous to donate cotton garments, such as dhotis.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>On Ganga Dussehra, Chant Mantras</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Ganga Dussehra is a sacred day, and you should fast in honour of Mother Ganga on this day. To get the blessings of Mother Ganges, say the mantra \"<strong>Om Namo Gangai Vishwaroopinayai Narayanayai Namo Namah</strong>\" on this auspicious occasion. The mother is happy as a consequence and bestows favorable outcomes on you.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Know about the Ganga Dussehra', 'Ganga Dussehra 2022: Learn about the ten sorts of sins that may be forgiven by taking a bath in the Ganges river on the occasion Ganga Dussehra, and how Ganga is revered in Hinduism.', 'Ganga Dussehra, Ganga Dussehra 2022, Ganga, Ganges river, Har Har gange, ganga darshan, Hrishikesh, Haridwar, Ganga Ghat, Aarti Darshan, Hinduism culture,', 1, 'know-about-the-ganga-dussehra', 'festivals', 'Ganga Dussehra, Ganga Dussehra 2022, Ganga, Ganges river, ganga darshan', '1653638745.jpg', 0, '2022-05-27 02:38:39', '2022-05-27 02:38:39'),
(164, 'Vastu Tips if you are Buying or Renting New Flat', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Vastu Shastra, an ancient Indian architectural discipline, has been used to&nbsp;find and design the optimum living places. Vastu-compliant residences&nbsp;and plots allow residents to enjoy happier, wealthier, healthier, and&nbsp;more prosperous lives. This ancient approach has gained traction in the&nbsp;real estate industry for locating the ideal locations, plots, and&nbsp;constructions for both residential and commercial reasons.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Apartment Entrance Vastu Advice</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A stylish entrance should always be the first consideration when&nbsp;analyzing the design plan or layout of a plot or a development (flat or&nbsp;apartment). The front door is the key to bringing joy and happiness to the entire&nbsp;household. A building\'s entrance can be found in 32 different places in&nbsp;each living area. Each of these 32 sites is significant in its own right and has a direct impact on our lives.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>For example, an entry in the&nbsp;southeast zone, often known as the Vastu zone of cash, causes payments&nbsp;to be delayed. A southwest entry is one of the least Vastu-compliant&nbsp;entrances and families that live there may have significant financial&nbsp;and relational problems.If you have an entrance in the north, on the other hand, you can expect&nbsp;substantial success in financial and business matters, as well as career opportunities. If the property or apartment you want to buy doesn\'t have a&nbsp;Vastu-compliant entrance, you can still buy it and use some simple Vastu remedies to make it Vastu-compliant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>A room layout that is Vastu Compatible</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When a room is placed correctly, you will get the most out of it. Depending on the zone in which it is located, each room has a beneficial or negative impact on the lives of the people who reside in it. A living&nbsp;room in the east zone, for example, is suitable for cultivating and&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>deepening social ties. Vastu, on the other hand, advises against placing a bedroom between the east and southeast. According to Vastu, sleeping&nbsp;in these zones causes tension and conflict with one\'s partner. A toilet&nbsp;should not be built between the house\'s north and northeast zones. It can harm the family\'s immunity and health. The southeast is a great&nbsp;location for kitchens. The northeast and southwest are not recommended&nbsp;for planning a kitchen.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Panchtattava, a five-element analysis</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>There are 16 zones or orientations in space that make up a dwelling environment. The zone has a major element that influences many elements of our lives.&nbsp;The north zone, for example, is dominated by water. Wealth, growth,&nbsp;career, monetary gains, and so forth are the key characteristics of this zone. As a result, any imbalance in this zone has a direct influence on</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;the residents\' professional, business, and financial health. Similarly, in the south zone, fire is the most influential element. Sleep and&nbsp;relaxation are the key features of the south zone.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>When buying a house, it\'s important to look at the layout of the various&nbsp;rooms and interior components. Kitchens, toilets, balconies, slopes,&nbsp;open spaces, water tanks, gardens, service lanes, neighbour\'s water&nbsp;storage, rainwater drainage, building height, shafts, and so on are all&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>examples of these. Water in the north, the air in the east, fire in the&nbsp;south, earth in the south-west, and space in the west — each of the five elements, or Panchtattava, must be present in its corresponding zone.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Apartment Vastu remedies&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>What if you\'ve already paid for a house or the deposit? such instance, you can employ Vastu’s fourth check-space programming.&nbsp;You don\'t need to dismantle or demolish your property if you use&nbsp;contemporary Vastu applications and procedures. You may balance the&nbsp;components in a zone using easy and efficient Vastu treatments and&nbsp;strategies. Colors, forms, lighting, metals, and symbols all work well&nbsp;in this regard.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The importance of Vastu examinations for apartments cannot be overstated.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Your Residence\'s Entrance</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Vastu Shastra advises against having a south or west entrance to your&nbsp;property. The reasoning for this is that the infrared rays that enter&nbsp;your home around noon will have a significant negative influence on your health. It is preferable to enter from the north or north-east. This&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>will ensure that you have sunlight in your home all day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Bedroom</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The most ideal bedroom is in the southwest corner. This is essential if you want to ensure that your house is a calm have where you can rest and&nbsp;relax while sleeping well. It is helpful to know that Vastu does not&nbsp;promote bedrooms that are irregularly formed. Therefore, you should look for square or rectangular rooms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Vastu and Kitchen Design</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>According to Vastu, the kitchen should face southeast. This ensures that food is processed in an easterly direction. It is not a smart idea to place the&nbsp;kitchen in front of the front entrance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>In flats, Vastu for children\'s rooms</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Consider putting your child\'s bedroom in the flat\'s northeast corner or&nbsp;northwest zone. In such circumstances, the windows should be on the&nbsp;north wall, since this allows for plenty of natural light while also&nbsp;preventing the entry of harmful infrared rays.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Your apartment\'s restrooms and toilets</strong> The majority of people overlook the flat\'s bathroom. It\'s crucial to&nbsp;determine if the bathroom/toilet is located in the flat\'s northwest or&nbsp;southeast corner. Also, keep the restrooms apart from the pooja room and the kitchen.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Vastu Tips if you are Buying or Renting New Flat- Astrology Kart', 'Vastu tips for buying or renting a new flat, Vastu tips for new homes, Vastu tips for new flat for rent', 'Vastu Shastra, Vastu Tips, Vastu 2022, Vastu For buying new home', 1, 'vastu-tips-if-you-are-buying-or-renting-new-flat', 'vastu', 'Vastu Shastra, Vastu Tips, Vastu 2022, Vastu For buying new home', '1654769928.jpg', 0, '2022-06-09 04:49:07', '2022-06-09 04:49:07'),
(165, 'When is Jagannath Rath Yatra in 2022, and what is an auspicious time to travel?', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>For Hindus, the Jagannath Rath Yatra 2022 is a significant holiday that is commemorated with considerable grandeur. Puri Rath Yatra, Rath Festival, and other names for Jagannath Rath Yatra (Jangganath yarta 2022). Lord Jagannath is honoured on this occasion. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat/astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer Online</a></strong>, It is also an annual event that takes place on the second day of the Ashadh Shukla Paksha. Puri Rath Yatra, the largest religious celebration in Puri, attracts tourists and devotees from all over India and the world. Every year, almost a million pilgrims flock to Puri to see the great chariot celebration.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The celebration recalls Lord Jagannath\'s annual visit to the famous \'Gundicha Temple,\' which is located near Balgandi Chaka in Puri while passing through the \'Mausi Maa Temple.\' During the Puri Rath Yatra, the temple\'s principal deities, Lord Jagannath, Goddess Subhadra, and Lord Balabhadra, are all brought in their respective chariots in a massive parade. Let us inform you that this year\'s Jagannath Yatra will take place on Friday, July 1, 2022.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Significance of Jagannath Rath Yatra (Jangganath yarta 2022)</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lord Jagannath, one of Lord Vishnu\'s avatars, is honoured during the Jagannath Rath Yatra event. Jagannath Temple is one of Hinduism\'s four primary pilgrimage sites, and it holds great religious significance. On the auspicious day of Puri Rath Yatra, devotees who are not permitted to enter the temple premises can see their deities.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>\'Ghosa Yatra,\' \'Dashvatar Yatra,\' \'Navadina Yatra,\' or \'Gundicha Yatra\' are some of the other names for this celebration. Puri\'s Rath Yatra is one of the most spectacular festivals that draw a large number of visitors. Anyone who takes part in the Puri Rath Yatra with sincerity is said to be set free from the cycle of life and death. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, A sighting of Lord Jagannath on his chariot is regarded as extremely lucky. It should be emphasized that these chariots are made from a particular wood each year, according to religious criteria.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Even the deities\' idols are constructed of wood and are religiously replaced every twelve years. The Puri Rath Yatra celebration represents unity and equality. It is one of the few events that is devoid of all types of prejudice. Muslims take part in this lovely chariot celebration as well.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Important dates for the 2022 Jagannath Rath Yatra</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>The sunrise begins at 5:48 a.m. and the sunset happens at ends at 7:12 p.m. on June 30, 2022.</li><li>The second date begins at 10.49 a.m. on June 30, 2022, and ends at 9.00 p.m. on June 1, 2022.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Jagannath Rath Yatra 2022 rituals</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Rath Yatra begins with unique prayers and ceremonies honouring the gods. The three principal deities, Goddess Subhadra, Lord Jagannath, and Lord Balabhadra, are then seated on their chariots. The \'Badadanda\' chariots, which are brilliantly painted, are then dragged through the streets of Puri.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>The most significant component of this rite is the chariot pulling. Devotees from all over the country go here with a tremendous desire to draw the Lord\'s chariot since this is a highly sacred deed.</li><li>The streets of Puri are packed with worshippers who have come to see their God. The procession arrives at the Gundicha temple, which is said to be Lord Jagannath\'s aunt\'s residence.</li><li>Pahad chhera On the first day of the Yatra, this is one of the most important ceremonies. The deities in this ceremony regard everyone as equal. The Gajapati King dons a sweeper\'s outfit and sweeps the area surrounding the deities and chariots with a gold-handed broom and sandalwood water with utmost dedication to executing this ceremony. This rite takes two days to complete.</li><li>The deities are carried to the Gundicha temple for the first time, and then returned to the Jagannath temple for the second time. The three goddesses are ceremonially bathed and clad in Boirani clothing when they arrive at the Gundicha temple.</li><li>Hera Panchami is the fourth day of the festival, which commemorates Goddess Lakshmi\'s arrival to Lord Jagannath.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>The importance of astrology</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lord Jagannath is one of Lord Vishnu\'s avatars, and the Jagannath Puri Rath Yatra is devoted to him. Jagannath Temple holds great religious importance for Hindus as one of their primary pilgrimages. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk/astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, On the occasion of the Puri Rath Yatra, devotees can have the darshan of the gods. Tourists and pilgrims flock to Puri during the Rath Yatra.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The Puri Car Festival is how international tourists refer to the Rath Yatra. It is thought that by participating in the Rath Yatra with complete dedication, a person will be liberated from the cycle of birth and death. The sheer sight of Lord Jagannath riding his chariot is considered fortunate, and these chariots are created each year using a unique sort of wood that meets religious standards. The idols of the deities are also made of wood, and they are replaced every 12 years. The Jagannath Puri Rath Yatra is a symbol of equality since it rises beyond all forms of discrimination.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Story</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>According to Hindu scriptures, the queens of Lord Krishna once asked Maa Rohini to reveal Lord Krishna\'s different Ras Leelas to the gopis. Before telling Lord Krishna\'s secret narrative, Rohini sent Subhadra to the door and refused to let anybody in. After a while, Krishna and Balarama arrived and stood on Subhadra\'s right and left sides at the door. They began to listen to Mata Rohini\'s account of Lord Krishna\'s boyhood adventures. Narada approached him as he was engrossed in the tales. When Narada saw the three brothers together, he prayed to the gods to bestow heavenly manifestations on them all in the same stance. As a result of Narada\'s prayer, he witnessed the divine manifestations of the three deities, and all three Jagannath temples are located in Puri.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'When is Jagannath Rath Yatra in 2022, and what is an auspicious time to travel? Important dates for the 2022 Jagannath Rath Yatra while travelling to Puri', 'When is Jagannath Rath Yatra in 2022, and what is an auspicious time to travel?', 'Lord Jagannath, Jagannath Rath Yatra 2022, Rath Yatra 2022, Rath Yatra, Jagannath, Vishnu, Krishna, Balaram, Subhadra, Puri Rath Yatra,', 1, 'when-is-jagannath-rath-yatra-in-2022-and-what-is-an-auspicious-time-to-travel', 'festivals', 'Jagannath Rath Yatra 2022, Rath Yatra 2022, Rath Yatra, Jagannath', '1655116082.jpg', 0, '2022-06-13 04:58:18', '2022-06-13 04:58:18');
