(169, 'Happy Guru Purnima - Astrology Kart', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Happy Guru Purnima 2022: </strong>This is a celebration to honor intellectual Gurus. Purnima is a full moon day, and Guru is a Sanskrit phrase that means \"darkness or ignorance remover.\" Guru Purnima is a Hindu, Buddhist, and Jain festival celebrated in India, Bhutan, and Nepal. Furthermore, on this auspicious day, devotees do pujas to gain the blessings of their Gurus.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Gurus or educators have a higher status in Hindu culture than God since it is these gurus and teachers that indicate the path that leads to God. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer Online</a></strong>, As a result, Guru Purnima is celebrated as a token of gratitude to all gurus and mentors. It is one of India\'s most celebrated Hindu festivities. Buddha\'s teachings are honored by both Hindus and Buddhists during Guru Purnima.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What is the concept of Guru Purnima?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The main purpose for celebrating Guru Purnima is to acknowledge teachers. There are several traditions associated with Guru Purnima. According to our holy scriptures, on this day that the first guru Adi Guru, Lord Shiva, started to teach yoga to the Saptrishis.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Hindus worship Ved Vyasa on Guru Purnima. Ved Vyasa is regarded as the most prominent Guru of the Vedic Period. He created the epic Mahabharata, crafted the four Vedas, and established several Puranas and ancient Hindu literature. Ved Vyasa is considered the first guru of the Hindu religion, and Guru Purnima is also referred to as Vyasa Purnima as a&nbsp;tribute.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Guru Purnima is also recognized as holy in Buddhism since it is stated that Lord Buddha offered his first teaching on this day in Sarnath, Uttar Pradesh.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mata, Pita, Guru, and Daivam is an ancient Sanskrit phrase. It indicates that the mother appears first, the father appears second, the Guru or teacher shows up third, and God appears fourth. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Talk to Best Astrologer in India</a></strong>,  Gurus are given considerably increased importance and respect, according to this term, since they come before God and have a higher position. The link between a guru and a shishya, or teacher and disciple, has been considered unique since ancient times.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Guru helps you achieve God by teaching you the importance of life. Without a guru, everyone\'s life would be terrible. As a result, numerous religions dedicate Guru Purnima in honor of their respective gurus. Hindus worship the famous sage Ved Vyas, while Buddhists honor Lord Buddha. On this day Jains remember Mahavira, one of the prominent Tirthankaras, and his followers. Nepalese and Bhutanese people also celebrate Guru Purnima.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Mischievous students have existed since the ancient period, while brilliant and intellectual professors or gurus have transformed the world. As a result, the holiday of Guru Purnima is held to remember the contributions of every guru who has or will ever exist on the earth.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The significance of Guru Purnima may be traced back to Hindu mythology. This mythology acknowledges this day as the day when Lord Shiva passed on his wisdom to his seven disciples. Since then, this occasion has been remembered to honor Lord Shiva, his instructive teachings, and his seven disciples.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A guru will help you learn more about the world and connect to it. Gurus help remove darkness from life and replace it with light. Complete surrendering to the guru has been considered the most significant virtue of a student from the ancient period. As a result, Guru&nbsp;Purnima is observed to pay gratitude to a guru, and the teachings of a guru are focused upon on this auspicious day.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>On the full moon day,&nbsp;people in India, Bhutan, and Nepal celebrate Guru Purnima. Thanks are expressed by students on this day to their teachers. Gurus represent the elimination of darkness from everyone\'s lives. Gurus bring&nbsp;value&nbsp;and enlightenment to their student\'s lives through their teachings. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong>,  On this auspicious day, people of all faiths honor their gurus by chanting and praying to the Guru Purnima Mantra. It is common for some people to abstain from salt, rice, and cereal-based meals on Guru Purnima. It is OK to eat plain yogurt and fruits. Food is sacrificed here in return for the guru\'s long life so that they might continue to receive guidance.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'Happy Guru Purnima - Astrology Kart', 'Guru Purnima is celebrated to acknowledge teachers and mentors. On this auspicious day, devotees do pujas to gain the blessings of their Gurus.', 'when is guru purnima, Guru Purnima 2022, Whatsapp messages, Quotes, wishes, Happy Guru Purnima, guru purnima july 2022, ashadh purnima 2022, Happy Guru Purnima 2022, Guru Purnima date, Guru Purnima 2022 date', 1, 'happy-guru-purnima-astrology-kart', 'festivals', 'Happy Guru Purnima, Guru Purnima 2022, ashadh purnima 2022,Happy Guru Purnima 2022', '1657702213.jpg', 0, '2022-07-13 03:48:51', '2022-07-13 03:48:51'),
(170, 'The Couple\'s 10 Most Common Married Life Issues', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Marriage is an auspicious connection between two individuals, yet it may also be the most uncomfortable relationship in someone\'s life. Occasionally spouses argue as soon as they marry, and sometimes they lose attraction to their relationship over time. There might be a variety of causes for quarrels, misunderstandings, and eventually animosity between spouses, but Astrology approaches marital difficulties from an entirely different angle.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Astrology can identify the source of a relationship issue and provide solutions. A difficult marriage is the result of negative planetary forces in our birth chart, which have ties to our former incarnations. Past life readings may help you understand why you are having marital troubles. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Talk to Best Astrologer in India</a></strong>, Using astrology to resolve marital issues can undoubtedly be helpful after a proper diagnosis and counseling. Several factors must be considered to make an accurate marriage prediction, which can only be done by a professional and scholar astrologer.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Marriage is the most important choice and should always be made after consulting with an astrologer. Most of the time, the primary cause of problems between spouses is a lack of mutual compatibility. Thus, it is recommended that everyone undergo Kundli matching before getting married to determine compatibility as well as the odds of the marriage\'s survival and success.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>To know life related issues <a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer</a></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Marriage astrology lists the ten most common marital difficulties. It is critical to understand that these issues may be resolved with competent astrological counsel.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Couple\'s Married Life Issues</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>1. <strong>Loss of interpersonal compatibility-</strong> When there is bhakoot dosha in the Kundli, couples struggle to comprehend each other. Both the janma nakshatra and the Rashi lords affect the mental pursuits of the inhabitants, so both must be in harmony for the couple to be compatible.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>2. <strong>Lack of Communication- </strong>In the early phases, the couple attempts to avoid arguing or addressing their issues. However, misconceptions accumulate over time, resulting in harsh relations between them. The position of Mercury and the second house will be significant here. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>3. <strong>Absolute dominance- </strong>A spouse may desire for his or her mate to be exactly like him or her. It is almost impossible, and couples begin to argue as a result of a lack of personal space in a relationship. Interference should be limited and should not overpower the romance of marriage.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>4. <strong>Extramarital affairs-</strong> Malefic planets with influences at the Lagna or Moon might cause any of the partners to engage in extramarital encounters. This is detrimental to the marriage.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>5. Financial aspects: </strong> A lack of financial success or monetary transparency can cause major problems in a marriage. The woman may expect her partner to provide financial stability for her, something the male partner may not do.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>6. <strong>Jealousy and pride-</strong> This occurs when both couples earn. One person may feel envious or insecure about the other person\'s better financial earnings or pay. This causes a gap between the life partners.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>7. <strong>Lacking personal intimacy-</strong> The spouses may lack sexual closeness due to overwork or exhaustion. This, in turn, leads to a troubled married life over time. By enhancing Venus, the karaka of romance and love in married life, astrology may aid to promote sexual closeness between spouses.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>8. <strong>Cultural differences</strong>- The spouses may come from different cultural backgrounds with distinct value systems. This might become the root of the spouses\' disputes and resentment.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>9. <strong>In-law interference-</strong> In certain circumstances, the female finds it difficult to adjust to her in-laws\' excessive meddling in their married connections. This eventually leads to a rift between the pair. For a native, the 4th and 10th homes are the houses of father-in-law and mother-in-law, respectively. An astrologer may suggest treatments to help couples improve their marriages by repairing their houses.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>10. <strong>Boredom or age difference-</strong> While most people consider age differences when choosing a partner, persons of various ages do marry in rare situations. As a result, there are variances in beliefs and tastes in life. The elder partner may appear uninteresting to the younger spouse, while the younger partner may appear childish to the older one.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>To get Astrology consultations online visit Astrology Kart and<a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\"> <strong>Chat with Astrologer</strong></a>.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'The Couple\'s 10Most Common Married Life Issues', '\"The decision to marry should always be taken after careful consideration\"  Advice based on astrology. The Couple\'s 10 Most Common Married Life Issues- Astrology Kart', 'Astrology Kart, Married Life Issues, Relationship problems, common married life issues, relationship astrology, astrology 2022, compatibility issues', 1, 'the-couples-10-most-common-married-life-issues', 'compatibility', 'compatibility issues, Astrology Kart, Married Life Issues, Relationship problems', '1636089008.jpg', 0, '2022-08-02 04:17:32', '2022-08-02 04:17:32'),
(171, 'What is the auspicious time to celebrate Raksha Bandhan?', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Raksha Bandhan Shubh Muhurat and Bhadra Time: Sawan Purnima Tithi and Bhadra Kaal are the traditional dates for the celebration of Raksha Bandhan. However, there is uncertainty this year over the Raksha Bandhan date. Raksha Bandhan will be celebrated this year on August 11th, according to some pandits and astrologers, while others advise waiting until August 12th to celebrate Rakhi. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer</a></strong>, There is uncertainty if a Hindu holiday or fast happens on two consecutive days.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The timing of the Rakhi event is in question once again this year since there are two full moon days on Raksha Bandhan. Astrologers and pandits alike offer varying recommendations regarding the date of Raksha Bandhan. This time, in addition to the date, Bhadra is also Raksha Bandhan\'s shadow. There will be a full day of Bhadra on August 11. The celebration of Raksha Bandhan should always be observed during a period when Bhadra is not present, according to the scriptures. Let us know what the Panchang and religious texts say about whether it is suitable to celebrate the Rakhi festival on August 11 and 12, given the circumstances.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>On August 11, Bhadra will spend the full day there.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The scriptures state that some times of the day are not deemed favorable for auspicious deeds. Rahu Kaal and Bhadra Kaal play significant roles in this. This time, on August 11, Sawan Purnima Tithi and Shravan Nakshatra would coincide with Bhadra Kaal for the whole day. At 8:53 p.m. on August 11, the unlucky period of Bhadra will come to an end.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>On August 11, Bhadra will not stay on Earth.</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Even though Bhadra will begin on August 11—the day of the full moon—his home will continue to be in Hades. According to the Muhurta Shastra Chintamani, while Bhadra is present on Earth, it is forbidden to perform auspicious or fortunate acts; but, when Bhadra is present in Patal Lok, it does not affect those who live on Earth. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong>, Bhadra has an impact on the world in which it exists. In this case, Raksha Bandhan may be observed on August 11 as Bhadra\'s dwelling is not on the planet.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The shadow of Bhadra falls on the earth whenever the Moon is in Cancer, Leo, Aquarius, or Pisces, according to calculations made by the Panchang. On the other hand, Bhadra lives in heaven when the Moon is in Aries, Taurus, or Scorpio.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Bhadra lives in Hades when the Moon is in Virgo, Libra, Sagittarius, or Capricorn. The scriptures state that there are no negative effects when Bhadra is housed in either Heaven or Hades. In this case, the festival of Raksha Bandhan shall be observed on August 11 due to Bhadra\'s residence in Hades.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Why not observe Raksha Bandhan on August 12th?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Raksha Bandhan is customarily observed on Sawan Purnima Tithi. Beginning at 10.38 am on August 11 and lasting till 07:05 am on August 12, respectively, Purnima Tithi will be followed by Pratipada Tithi of Bhadrapada. <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a></strong>, Raksha Bandhan is not specifically celebrated on August 12 for any unique reason.11 August Raksha Bandhan auspicious time - Raksha Bandhan Shubh Muhurat Timing 2022</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The Muhurta calculation predicts that Abhijit Muhurta will be present on August 11 from 11.37 to 12.29. A Vijay Muhurta will take place on Thursday, August 11, from 02:14 to 03:07 p.m. Rakhi can be fastened in this way during Bhadrakal.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Raksha Bandhan with Bhadra</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>06.18 a.m. to 08:00 a.m. Raksha Bandhan Bhadra Mukha</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>At 8:51 p.m., Raksha Bandhan Bhadra Kaal concludes.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Choghadiya Shubh Muhurta - 11 August 2022</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;Morning Muhurat: 6:00 AM -7:39AM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Variable days Muhurat: 10:53 AM – 12:31 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Profit Days Muhurat: 12:31 PM – 2:08 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Amrit Days Muhurat: 02:08 PM - 03.46 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Good Evening Muhurat: 05.23 PM – 7:10 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Amrit Ratri Muhurat: 7:00 PM - 08.23 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Variable Night Muhurat: 8:23 PM – 09:46 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Scorpio Ascendant Days Muhurat: 01.33 PM - 03.23 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Raksha Bandhan 2022 Pradosh Muhurta</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Pradosh Muhurta: 20:52:15 PM to 21:13:18 PM</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'What is the auspicious time to celebrate Raksha Bandhan? - Astrology Kart', 'What is the auspicious time to celebrate Raksha Bandhan? Here are some specific times when you can do all the deities.- Astrology Kart', 'Raksha Bandhan, Rakhi 2022, Muhurat for rakhi, Raksha Bandhan Muhurat 2022, Raksha Bandhan Muhurat', 1, 'what-is-the-auspicious-time-to-celebrate-raksha-bandhan', 'festivals', 'Raksha Bandhan, Rakhi 2022, Muhurat for rakhi, Raksha Bandhan Muhurat 2022, Raksha Bandhan Muhurat', '1660121730.jpg', 0, '2022-08-10 03:25:47', '2022-08-10 03:25:47'),
(172, 'Har Ghar Tiranga - Astrology Kart', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>India has been free of British colonialism for 75 years. Many British and European scholars predicted that India would not be able to sustain its freedom for a long time when India became independent. In the last 75 years, a culturally diverse nation has succeeded in creating a nation-state with a democracy based on popular representation. There have been difficult times, there are now difficult times, and there are numerous difficulties.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a></strong> if you want to know how you will succeed in your business.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>In the middle of all of this, it is a chance to reflect on the struggle for freedom. It is a chance to put our democracy to the test, and also to honor our accomplishments.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The \"<strong>Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav</strong>\" is a planned countrywide celebration of this accomplishment by the Indian government. A campaign to raise the tricolor national flag at their houses from August 13 to August 15 this year has been launched by the countrymen. It has been the same as always. This serves to raise awareness of the national flag and incite a sense of patriotism among the citizens. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>For more <strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/\">Astrology Advice Online</a> </strong>visit Astrology Kart.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Here, it is important to remember that each house\'s tricolor represents a public campaign rather than a rule or policy.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>How do you participate in the Har Ghar Tiranga Abhiyan?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>The administration wants people to hoist the tricolor on more than 20 crore homes. It will feature public and private buildings in addition to ordinary people\'s homes.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>To guarantee the availability of flags throughout the nation, the government has taken several actions:</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\r\n<ol type=\"1\"><li>Sales of the national flag will begin on August 1, 2022, at all post offices around the nation.</li><li>&nbsp;Contracts for the procurement and sale of flags have been made by state governments with a variety of partners. &nbsp;It is also registered on the Gem Portal that the Indian National Flag is displayed.</li></ol>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>To speed up the process of delivering the flag, the Indian government has partnered with several e-commerce companies and self-help organizations.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>Post offices are another place to buy flags. In post offices, the cost of the flag remains at Rs 25.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>Through digital India people may participate in this campaign digitally.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li>For people to show their patriotism, the Ministry of Culture has established the website <a href=\"https://harghartiranga.com/ \">https://harghartiranga.com/ </a>where they may \"pin the flag\" and take a \"selfie with the flag.\" The nation\'s inhabitants have also been urged to display the tricolor on their social media sites between August 2 and August 15.</li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What are state governments doing?</strong><strong></strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Many state governments have specific plans for this occasion. To make