paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/talk-to-astrologer\">Talk to Astrologer </a>to know more mythological tales of Lord krishna</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What is done on Janmashtami?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>A fast is kept on this day to glorify Lord Krishna. All problems are said to be resolved by Lord Shri Krishna. On this day, fasting and worship are ways to get blessings. On this day, prasad is given out following the devotion.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>When is Janmashtami Vrat in 2022?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>This year, some individuals will observe the fast on August 18 in observance of the Udayatithi, while others will observe it on August 19 in observance of the fast. Janmashtami is a very sacred holiday, hence there are some foods that should not be consumed on that day. Even if you forget, you shouldn\'t consume meat or alcohol on this day. On this day, avoid eating anything tamasic.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What to eat on Janmashtami?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Juicy fruits are recommended for those who observe a fast on this day. Additionally, during the fast, care should be made to ensure that the body has enough water. One may also consume other fruits.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What water may one drink on Janmashtami?</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>According to tradition, one can break their fast on this day by consuming either curd or water. Following that, you can eat.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://astrologykart.com/chat-with-astrologer\">Chat with Astrologer</a> to know when is the